<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Lubricating Oil Pump, Oil
        Filter, and Cooler - Remove - Remove Oil Filter and Header
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010902.3" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Remove Oil Filter and Header</title>
        <para id="s210010902.3.1">Oil filter cartridge and oil header must be removed prior to mounting engine on a
            stand.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Drain coolant from engine, if removing oil filter and cooler header.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove oil feed supply tube nut on top of oil filter header. Remove and discard
                tube nut O-ring. Cap fitting on header for protection.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010909" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove oil supply tube</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove oil filter cartridge. Discard oil filter cartridge according to local
                regulations.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Some severe service units have a short oil filter with an adapter installed inside the oil filter
                    housing. Do not remove this adapter.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f210010910" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove oil filter</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one water coolant supply tube bolt and retainer plate from crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil cooler assembly mounting hardware from crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010911" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove oil cooler mounting bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolts</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly from crankcase. Discard
                O-rings, gaskets, and seals.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010912" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove oil cooler</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
